09:14.429 --> 09:15.555
<i>and clip them off.</i>

09:17.932 --> 09:19.642
- How many tools
did this guy bring?

09:19.642 --> 09:20.894
He's got his own hammer.

09:20.894 --> 09:22.187
He's got his own
fullering tool.

09:22.187 --> 09:23.855
- He's got
chainmail mittens.

09:23.855 --> 09:25.857
<i>- This is my fig bucker.</i>

09:25.857 --> 09:28.610
I like it because I can hit
things really hard with it.

09:28.610 --> 09:30.528
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:30.528 --> 09:31.529
- There it is!

09:32.864 --> 09:34.657
Strike!

09:34.657 --> 09:38.244
<i>- Forging allows me</i>
<i>to solve my problems</i>

09:38.244 --> 09:40.622
by setting stuff on fire

09:40.622 --> 09:42.957
and then promptly beating
the crap out of it,

09:42.957 --> 09:44.793
<i>and I love that.</i>

09:44.793 --> 09:48.254
- Bladesmiths,
two hours has elapsed!

09:48.254 --> 09:50.757
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:50.757 --> 09:52.801
- I realize that the shape
is almost there,

09:52.801 --> 09:54.427
and I don't really want
to keep messing with it,

09:54.427 --> 09:56.554
<i>so it's time to quench.</i>

09:56.554 --> 09:59.224
<i>[driving rock music]</i>

09:59.224 --> 10:01.309
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:01.309 --> 10:03.561
- Todd just put that knife
into the quench oil.

10:03.561 --> 10:06.189
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:06.189 --> 10:07.232
- There's no warpage in it.

10:07.232 --> 10:09.109
Aha!

10:09.109 --> 10:10.902
